            <h2>About</h2>
            <p class="lead">
                Neighborly is a crowdsourcing-based resource guide created by Project for Healing, Inc. and
                WeaveTales to help immigrants, refugees, and low-income families in Northeast Florida better
                navigate the resources available in their areas. Neighborly features the locations and information
                on providers of core services such as food, housing, and legal aid. The website is accessible through
                a direct URL: <a href="http://neighborlyguide.org" target="_blank">neighborlyguide.org</a>​ or <a href="http://neighborly.guide" target="_blank">​neighborly.guide​.</a>
            </p>
            <p class="lead">
                Neighborly runs on information crowdsourced by the users and service providers. The website will
                have submission links where users and service providers could add information. Our staff at WeaveTales will
                screen all submissions on a regular basis and publish them online. If needed, the person submitting the information
                or the service providers will be contacted to ensure the accuracy and quality of the information on the website before
                making it public. Some of these screening and approval processes will take place at the monthly user meetings that WeaveTales will host.
                Anyone interested in using or currently using Neighborly is welcome to join the meeting. The dates and locations of the meetings
                may vary each month and will be posted on <a href="http://www.weavetales.org/events​" target="_blank">www.weavetales.org/events​</a> and our Twitter account (<a href="https://twitter.com/neighborlyguide​" target="_blank">twitter.com/neighborlyguide</a>).
            </p>
            <p class="lead">To learn more about Neighborly and how you can contribute, please contact us at (904) 990-4821 or basma@weavetales.org.</p>
