            <h2>History</h2>
            <p class="lead">
                Against the backdrop of drastic budget cuts at the federal level since 2017, immigrant and refugee communities, as well as many low-income families,
                have been gradually turned away from various social services that have helped their successful integration to the American society for the past two generations. Unfortunately,
                Jacksonville and Northeast Florida have been no exception to this growing challenge. The lack of access to adequate services reportedly led to a number of newcomers and low-income
                households falling victim to scams and unethical business practices over the years.
            </p>
